name: Powers in addition to other powers
text: §382-10  Powers in addition to other powers.  The powers conferred by this chapter shall be in addition and supplemental to the powers conferred by any other law, including sections 125-1 to 125-7 and nothing herein shall be construed as limiting any other powers of the governor or the designated agency mentioned in section 382-3. [L 1951, c 209, §10; RL 1955, §92-11; HRS §382-10]
